# BUJA - Cursor Rules

## Core
1. Minimal context - read only needed files
2. Tests required for all changes
3. Korean responses, English code comments
4. Update guides when structure changes

## Stack
- Python 3.10+, Streamlit, uv, SQLAlchemy
- WSL environment

## Structure
```
BUJA/
├── app.py              # Main entry
├── pages/              # Streamlit pages (8 files)
├── src/                # Source
│   ├── agents/         # LLM agents
│   ├── analyzers/      # Portfolio/risk analysis
│   ├── external/       # External APIs (LLM)
│   ├── middleware/     # Auth, error handling
│   ├── models/         # SQLAlchemy models
│   ├── repositories/   # Data access
│   ├── services/       # Business logic
│   └── utils/          # Utilities
├── tests/              # unit/integration/e2e
├── config/             # Settings
└── docs/               # Documentation
```

## Key Files
- `.cursor/ARCHITECTURE.md` - System design
- `.cursor/DEVELOPMENT.md` - Dev rules
- `docs/REQUIREMENTS.md` - Requirements (503 lines)
- `docs/DESIGN.md` - Detailed design (1719 lines)

## Notes
- Large docs: reference sections only
